        "title": "US stocks sink this week, semiconductors walloped amid sell-off",
        "description": "<p>US equities (<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"\" class=\"link\" href=\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EDJI?p=%5EDJI&.tsrc=fin-srch\" data-i13n=\"slk:^DJI;cpos:1;pos:1\">^DJI</a>, <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"\" class=\"link\" href=\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EIXIC?p=%5EIXIC&.tsrc=fin-srch\" data-i13n=\"slk:^IXIC;cpos:2;pos:1\">^IXIC</a>, <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"\" class=\"link\" href=\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EGSPC?p=%5EGSPC&.tsrc=fin-srch\" data-i13n=\"slk:^GSPC;cpos:3;pos:1\">^GSPC</a>) closed Friday's session in negative territory — led by the Nasdaq Composite's 1.4% drop — all three of the market indexes seeing weekly losses amid the recent sell-off in semiconductor stocks.</p>\n<p>Yahoo Finance Markets and Data Editor <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"\" class=\"link\" href=\"https://www.yahoo.com/author/jared-blikre/\" data-i13n=\"slk:Jared Blikre;cpos:4;pos:1\">Jared Blikre</a> examines the day's market moves, taking a closer look at the losses in semiconductor stocks and the gains seen across the software landscape.</p>",
